      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask which office location works best for the appointment.\n\nNewtown's locations:\n- Elmhurst — 87-10 51st Ave, Elmhurst, NY 11373\n- Brooklyn — 761 55th St., Brooklyn, NY 11220\n- Manhattan — 198 Canal St., New York, NY 10013\n- Flushing — 37-12 Prince Street, Flushing, NY 11354\n- SoHo Endo Ambulatory Surgery Center — 168 Centre Street, New York, NY 10013\n- Great Neck — 440-450 Northern Boulevard, Great Neck, NY 11021\n\nSay something like:\n\"We have six locations, Elmhurst, Brooklyn, Manhattan, Flushing, SoHo Endo Ambulatory Surgery Center, and Great Neck. Which one works the best?\"\n\nIf they have no preference: \"No problem — I'll note that either location works and the team can schedule whichever has availability first.\"\n\nIf {{appointment_for}} is \"other\" and the caller doesn't know which location:\n\"That's okay — I'll note that either works and the team can confirm with them when they call back.\"\n\nIf the user refuses to engage or wants to skip:\n\"No worries — I'll leave it open and the clinic will find the most convenient option.\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice. If the caller doesn't know or has no preference, accept it and move on."
      }
    },
